Step 1: Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities can be obtained as Total Liabilities and Owner's Equity minus Total Owner's Equity:  
  Total Liabilities = 14,066,175.95 – 11,330,150.23 = 2,736,025.72  
• Total Assets at period end = 14,066,175.95  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
  = 2,736,025.72 / 14,066,175.95 ≈ 0.1946  
Rounded off, we get 0.19

Step 2: Calculate Gross Profit Margin  
• From the income statement:  
  Gross Profit = 1,340,513.79  
  Total Revenue = 6,920,513.79  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (1,340,513.79 / 6,920,513.79) × 100 ≈ 19.35%  

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio  
• From the cash flow statement:  
  Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -5,714,107.45  
• From the balance sheet:  
  Total Current Liabilities = 2,736,025.72  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities  
  = -5,714,107.45 / 2,736,025.72 ≈ -2.087  
Rounded off, this is -2.09

Thus, the final solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.19", 
    "Gross Profit Margin": "19.35%", 
    "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-2.09"
  }
}
